type.description:

Represents a task which is executable by Gradle. 

<p>Note: <a href='type://Task'>Task</a> extends <a href='type://Launchable'>Launchable</a> since 1.12.</p> 

@since 1.0-milestone-3

method.description:

Returns the description of this task, or <a href='type://null'>null</a> if it has no description. 

<br><br><b class='return'>returns:</b>The description of this task, or <a href='type://null'>null</a> if it has no description. 
@since 1.0-milestone-3


Returns the group a task belongs to. 

<br><br><b class='return'>returns:</b>the group a task belongs to. 
@since 2.5


Returns the name of this task. Note that the name is not necessarily a unique identifier for the task. 

<br><br><b class='return'>returns:</b>The name of this task. 
@since 1.0-milestone-3


Returns the path of this task. This is a fully qualified unique name for this task. 

<br><br><b class='return'>returns:</b>The path of this task. 
@since 1.0-milestone-3

